<module>
  <title><m>-(e)achd</m> noun-deriving suffix</title>
  <p></p>
  <p><strong>-(e)achd</strong> is a suffix used to create feminine <a href="?xx=nouns/derived_common_nouns">derived common nouns</a> 
    from <a href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjectives</a> or other common nouns.</p>
  <p>De-adjectival examples –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>geur</i> <en>bitter, sharp</en> ⇒ <m>geurachd</m> <en>asperity</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chneasta</i> <en>cruel, merciless</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chneastachd</m> <en>cruelty, mercilessness</en></li>
    <li><i>mì-chuanta</i> <en>untidy</en> ⇒ <m>mì-chuantachd</m> <en>untidiness</en></li>
    <li><i>naomh</i> <en>holy</en> ⇒ <m>naomhachd</m> <en>holiness</en></li>
    <li><i>sleamhainn</i> <en>slippery</en> ⇒ <m>sleamhnachd</m> <en>slipperiness</en></li>
  </ul>
  <p>De-nominal examples –</p>
  <ul>
    <li><i>gobha</i> <en>metalsmith</en> (genitive <i>gobhainn</i>) ⇒ <m>goibhneachd</m> <en>metalsmithing</en></li>
    <li><i>mùtaire</i>, <i>cùl-mhùtaire</i> <en>smuggler</en> ⇒ <m>mùtaireachd</m>, <m>cùl-mhùtaireachd</m> <en>smuggling</en></li>
  </ul>
</module>

